  "response": "Here are several government schemes and support for SC/ST startups in India:\n\n1. Government Schemes\n- Startup India\n- Stand-Up India\n- MSME schemes\n- SC/ST Hub initiative\n\n2. Financial Support\n- Credit Guarantee Fund\n- Subsidized loans\n- Venture capital assistance\n- Collateral-free loans\n\n3. Key Institutions\n- National SC/ST Hub\n- NITI Aayog\n- Startup India\n- Department of Empowerment of Persons with Disabilities\n\n4. Steps to Apply\n- Register your startup\n- Prepare business plan\n- Get SC/ST certificate\n- Apply through official portals\n\n5. Documentation Required\n- Aadhaar card\n- Caste certificate\n- Business plan\n- Company registration\n- Bank documents\n\n6. Online Platforms\n- www.startupindia.gov.in\n- www.msme.gov.in\n- www.standupmitra.in\n\n7. Additional Benefits\n- Interest subsidies\n- Tax exemptions\n- Skill development training\n- Marketing support\n\n8. Recommended Process\n- Research schemes\n- Consult local SC/ST development offices\n- Prepare comprehensive documents\n- Apply systematically\n\nThorough research and proper documentation are crucial for successful application.",
